Pictures, Inc.; Radio Pictures)  aCopyright catalog, motion pictures, 1912-1939:bp. 543 (Millie, 1931; RKO Radio Pictures, Inc.; 6Feb31; LP1984)  aEncycl. Brittanica, via WWW, Jan. 13, 2011b(RKO Radio Pictures, Inc.; formed in merger of the Radio Corporation of America, Keith-Albee-Orpheum theatre chain, and American Pathé productions in 1928)1 aRKO Radio Pictures was a motion picture production and distribution company. The company was originally established in 1929 as Radio Pictures during the founding of Radio-Keith-Orpheum Corporation. In early 1931 some feature films were produced as Radio Pictures, but by the end of 1931, RKO Radio Pictures seems to have been the main producing entity. It also existed concurrently with RKO Pathe. In 1955 the company merged with General Teleradio to form RKO Teleradio Pictures, but continued to produce features through 1957.  aRETRO03581cz  a2200565n  188831920220423064536.0790521n| azannaabn          |b ana        an  79043101 zn  81129871 zsh 85144982   a(OCoLC)oca00276531  aDLCbengerdacDLCdDLCdDLC-HdDLCdOCoLCdUPBdWaUdIEN  s1929t19862 aC388555 Walt Disney Productions  aMotion picture studios2lcsh  cUnited States2naf  aMotion pictures--Production and direction2lcsh  aTelevision program production  aeng2 aDisney Film Recording Company2 aDisney Productions2 aDisney Studios0 wnnaaaDisney (Walt) Productions2 aUlpane Ṿolṭ Disni2 aUlpene Ṿolṭ Disni2 aṾolṭ Disni (Firm)2 aWalt Disney Studio2 aWalt Disney Studios (1929-1986)2 aאולפני וולט דיסני2 aאלפני וולט דיסני2 aוולד דיסני2 aוולט דיסני2 aסרטי וולט דיסני2 wriPredecessor:aDisney Brothers Studio2 wriPredecessor:aWalt Disney Enterprises2 wriPredecessor:aLiled Realty and Investment Company, ltd.2 wriSuccessor:aWalt Disney Company  aMachine-derived non-Latin script reference project.  aNon-Latin script references not evaluated.  aIts The adventures of Mickey Mouse, c1931.  aTel. 